description=<p>The examples in this section look at some of the techniques you can use to process text and data.  Examples include how to search, replace or combine text.</p>
entries=Text search box\nInserting some text before each line in a field\nCombine random text strings\nRepeating a string of text\nReplacing a text style in a field\nEditing the clipboard\nConverting a relative path to an absolute path\nConverting an absolute path to a relative path\nConverting between characters and numerical (ASCII) values\nFinding common lines in two containers\nFinding lines that are not common to two containers\nListing all the handlers in a script\nListing all the unique words in a piece of text\nRemoving bold text styles from a field\nReversing text\nRounding a number up to a ceiling\nSorting a list\nSwitching between styled text and HTML source\nCompare numbers approximately\nDisplaying a count down (blocking)\nStoring a modification timestamp\nDisplaying a count down (non-blocking)\nTranslating a color name to an RGB numeric triplet
name=Processing Text and Data
title=Processing Text and Data